    "In the DQL algorithm, we were utilizef V π (Si) to denote the total reward under a given policy π.V π (Si) = ri + γri+1 + γ 2 ri+2 + L (7)The DQL algorithm computes the Q value to assess a specific state and activity.",
    "This value is determined by considering both immediate and discounted rewards.",
    "The formulation of the Q value is as follows: The discount coefficient, denoted by γ (0 < γ < 1), represents the impact of future rewards on the current activity.",
    "The objective of Q learning is to optimize the overall utility.",
    "Therefore, in ( 8), we substitute the variables ri and V π (Si+1) with the values Oi and max Qa i+1,∈A (Si+1, ai+1), respectively.Q (si, ai) ← ri + γV r (Si+1)(8)Q (si, ai) ← Oi + γ maxQa i+1,∈A (Si+1, ai+1)(9)Here, A represents the collection of action sets."
